&lt;p&gt;DataDome is a global leader in bot and cyberfraud protection, trusted by some of the world’s largest brands to protect their digital assets from automated threats. As AI agents, autonomous LLMs, and sophisticated bots become more prevalent, DataDome is at the forefront of introducing&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;new trust and security solutions to the market the age of AI-driven traffic&lt;/strong&gt;. As a PMM at DataDome, you’ll be able to make a real impact in a fast-growing, mission-driven company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⭐ About the team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every Product Marketing Manager (PMM) at DataDome plays a highly visible, strategic and cross-functional role in our journey. Our team that operates in a fast-paced, collaborative, and fun culture that is excited about helping customers protect themselves against sophisticated bots and cyberfraud. Reporting to the Senior Director of Product Marketing, you will be based in our NYC or Paris office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This new role enables you to collaborate with world-class product and marketing teams, translating complex technical capabilities into clear customer value and category leadership. You will own how DataDome defines and enables trusted relationships in a world of AI agents, where ecommerce will begin to transition from direct human to agent-to-agent interactions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll lead the go-to-market strategy and execution throughout the product lifecycle, creating impactful product messaging and collateral, enabling sales and partner teams, and supporting evangelism and demand generation efforts with the marketing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your scope:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;👉 &lt;strong&gt;You will be more specifically in charge of things like...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve DataDome’s product positioning and messaging for AI-driven threats, agent trust, and anti-fraud solutions. Develop a deep understanding of AI agents, bots, LLM-driven automation, and emerging trust frameworks. Conduct market and competitive analysis to identify differentiation and white-space opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create marketing &amp;amp; communication plan for new product launches and feature releases aligned to the target audiences. Create compelling, differentiated value propositions, use cases &amp;amp; narratives with a clear understanding of target customer personas’ needs and core capabilities of the offering.&lt;/li&gt;
